graph LR
    subgraph Data Lifecycle
        UPLOAD[New Data Upload] --> STANDARD[S3 Standard]

        STANDARD -->|30 days| IA[S3 Intelligent-Tiering]
        IA -->|Auto-optimize| IA1[Frequent Access Tier]
        IA -->|Auto-optimize| IA2[Infrequent Access Tier]
        IA -->|Auto-optimize| IA3[Archive Instant Access]

        STANDARD -->|90 days<br/>if not accessed| SIA[S3 Standard-IA]

        SIA -->|180 days| GLACIER[S3 Glacier Flexible]
        IA2 -->|180 days| GLACIER

        GLACIER -->|1 year| DEEP[S3 Glacier Deep Archive]

        DEEP -->|7 years| DELETE[Delete After Retention]
    end

    subgraph Storage Class Comparison
        direction TB

        STANDARD --> COST1[Cost: $$$$<br/>Retrieval: Immediate<br/>Use: Hot data, <30 days]

        IA1 --> COST2[Cost: $$$<br/>Retrieval: Immediate<br/>Use: Auto-managed]

        SIA --> COST3[Cost: $$<br/>Retrieval: Immediate<br/>Min: 30 days storage<br/>Use: Infrequent access]

        GLACIER --> COST4[Cost: $<br/>Retrieval: 1-5 hours<br/>Min: 90 days storage<br/>Use: Archive, compliance]

        DEEP --> COST5[Cost: $<br/>Retrieval: 12 hours<br/>Min: 180 days storage<br/>Use: Long-term archive]
    end

    subgraph Cost Optimization Rules
        direction TB

        R1[Bronze Layer:<br/>30d Standard → 90d Glacier → 2y Delete]
        R2[Silver Layer:<br/>90d Standard → 1y IA → Archive]
        R3[Gold Layer:<br/>Keep in Standard/IA<br/>Business-critical data]
        R4[Logs & Raw:<br/>7d Standard → 30d IA → 90d Glacier → 1y Delete]
        R5[Backups:<br/>Immediate to Glacier<br/>7y retention → Delete]
    end

